<dt class="dlterm">25</dt>

<dd class="dlentry"><p>Only one materialized query table can be specified for a SET INTEGRITY statement.</p>
</dd>


<dt class="dlterm">26</dt>

<dd class="dlentry"><p>The database partition group being redistributed contains at least one replicated materialized query table.</p>
</dd>


<dt class="dlterm">27</dt>

<dd class="dlentry"><p>A replicated materialized query table cannot be defined on a table that does not have a unique index existing on one or more columns that make up the replicated materialized query table.</p>
</dd>


<dt class="dlterm">28</dt>

<dd class="dlentry"><p>A typed table or materialized query table cannot be renamed.</p>
</dd>


<dt class="dlterm">29</dt>

