<p>Note that both the db2rfe command and the db2iupdt command require that the database manager instance be stopped and restarted.</p>

<p><strong>sqlcode</strong>:  -1639</p>

<p><strong>sqlstate</strong>:  08001</p>','explanation' => '<p>The DB2 database system requires that your instance and database directories, and the files in those directories, have a minimum level of operating system permissions. When the instance and database directories are created by the database manager the permissions are accurate, and changing those permissions could cause database manager functions to fail. The complexity of DB2 file permissions is increased in the case of non-root installed instances and operating system-based authentication.</p>

