<dd class="dlentry"><p>The range overlaps with another partition. Each data partition must  have a well defined starting and ending boundary and each data value must go into one and  only one data partition. Also, if the same value (except MINVALUE or MAXVALUE) is used in the  ending bound of one partition and the starting bound of the next partition, then at least  one of these bounds must be defined as EXCLUSIVE. For an existing table, to determine whether the bounds of a partition  are INCLUSIVE or EXCLUSIVE, query the SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS catalog table as follows  (substituting the appropriate values for &#39;table-schema&#39; and &#39;table-name&#39;):</p>

