<li>If the statement is one that creates or modifies a packed description, the new packed description might be too large for the corresponding column in the system catalogs.</li>
</ul>

<p>This message can also be returned when an attempt is made to execute an SQL statement that is too complex to compile.  For example, the following elements contribute to the complexity of a statement:</p>

<ul>
<li>Constraints, such as table check constraints or foreign key constraints</li>

<li>Triggers</li>

<li>Row access controls and column access controls</li>
</ul>

